    \title Create Qt projects

    To create a project, select or create a preset for a particular project type:

    \list 1
        \li Go to \uicontrol {Command Palette}, and then select
            \uicontrol {Qt: Create New Project}.
        \li In \uicontrol {New Project}, enter a name for the project.
            \image vscodeext-create-new-project.webp {New Project dialog}
        \li In \uicontrol {Terminal}, select a preset or
            \uicontrol {Manually select features} to create your own preset.
            \image vscodeext-create-new-project-pick-preset-widgets.webp {Pick a preset in Terminal}
        \li Select a CMake kit for the project.
    \endlist

    \section1 Project presets

    Select one of the following project presets:

    \list
        \li \c {[Default] @projects/cpp/console} creates a basic console
            application without a GUI.
        \li \c {[Default] @projects/cpp/qtquick} creates a simple \l {Qt Quick}
            application with one QML file (.qml).
        \li \c {[Default] @projects/cpp/qwidget} creates a simple \l {Qt Widgets}
            application with one form (.ui).
        \li \c {[Manually select features]} creates a new preset with the
            default values you select.
    \endlist

    \section1 Create a project preset

    Select \uicontrol {Manually select features} to create a project preset with
    the following settings.

    \table
    \header
        \li Setting
        \li Possible values
    \row
        \li Project type
        \li The type of the project to create:
            \list
                \li \c {[Default] @projects/cpp/console}
                \li \c {[Default] @projects/cpp/qtquick}
                \li \c {[Default] @projects/cpp/qwidget}
            \endlist
    \row
        \li Use form?
        \li Whether to create a UI form for the project: \uicontrol Y (Yes) or
            \uicontrol N (No).
    \row
        \li Use translation?
        \li Whether to add Qt translation source files (TS) to the project:
            \uicontrol Y (Yes) or \uicontrol N (No).
    \row
        \li Target language
        \li A language and territory (locale).
    \row
        \li Save for later use?
        \li Whether to save the settings as a preset: \uicontrol Y (Yes) or
            \uicontrol N (No).
    \row
        \li Enter the preset name
        \li Enter a name for the preset. The preset list shows it at the top
            the next time you create a new project.
    \endtable

    \sa {Tutorial: Qt Widgets application}, {Add files to projects}
